CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in the Pittsburgh Coruier newspaper, October 18, 1952, pg. 1 reads: "Homestead Probe Figures - Benny Buford (left) and Milton (Coast) Blount went on trial Tuesday with Homestead Police Chief Thomas (Muck) Conlin charged with conspiracy to extort.  The charges were lodged against Buford, a Homestead policeman, and Blount as a result of the recent special grand jury investigation. - Teenie Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Homestead police officer Benny Buford, and Milton "Coast" Blount, standing in front of stone wall
